he eternity of the world. It will be important for anyone interested in the development and transition of ideas from the late ancient world onwards.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 4aNeoplatonismus. 4aProclus. 4aProklos. 4aRezeption. 4aneoplatonism. 4areception. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh1 aButorac, David D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLayne, Danielle, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2017z9783110547733oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104703760 cprintz978311046699740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110471625zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110471625zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110471625.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3 DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-DGDb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017